Name: autosomal dominant hypocalcemia 1
Definition: An autosomal dominant hypocalcemia disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the calcium sensing receptor gene (CASR) on chromosome 3q21.

Name: autosomal dominant hypocalcemia 2
Definition: An autosomal dominant hypocalcemia that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the G protein subunit alpha 11 gene (GNA11) on chromosome 19p13.
